This topic describes how to configure an external load balancer for the <%= vars.control_plane %>.

## <a id='overview'></a> Overview

You must configure an external load balancer to make the <%= vars.control_plane %> accessible from outside the network.
This external load balancer forwards traffic to the <%= vars.control_plane %> endpoint on ports 8443 and 9021.
You can use any external load balancer for the <%= vars.control_plane %>.

To set up an external load balancer for the <%= vars.control_plane %>, do the following after you install the <%= vars.product_tile %> tile:

1. [Retrieve the <%= vars.control_plane %> Endpoint](#retrieve-tkgi-api)
1. [Configure an External Load Balancer](#loadbalancer-tkgi-api)

## <a id='prerequisites'></a> Prerequisites

Before configuring an external load balancer for the <%= vars.control_plane %>, you must have the following:

* The <%= vars.control_plane %> certificate that you provided in the **<%= vars.product_tile %>** tile > **<%= vars.control_plane %>** > **Certificate to secure the <%= vars.control_plane %>**.
* The <%= vars.control_plane %> hostname that you entered in the **<%= vars.product_tile %>** tile > **<%= vars.control_plane %>** > **API Hostname (FQDN)**.

